15/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The minor government partner Democratic Union for Integration said on Monday (14 June) that it wants the ruling coalition to open debate on defining Skopje as a bilingual municipality. 
The proposed measure is part of a decentralisation package, considered vital to holding local elections this autumn.
In other news Monday, Turkish Interior Minister Abdul Kadir Aksu met with his Macedonian counterpart, Siljan Avramovski, in Skopje. 
Aides say they agreed on the need to revise and expand a co-operation protocol signed by the countries in 1992. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, MIA - 15/06/04; A1 TV - 14/06/04)
